    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-01-23T07:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-01-23T07:00:00-05:00" n="295"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d295">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00118 European War 1939/71: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Bulgaria</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Earle</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Sofia</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-01-23T14:00:00+02:00"
                            >January 23, 1941—2 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received January 24—5:32 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>31. Colonel Donovan arrived at a most crucial time. His forceful declaration to
                    the King and his Ministers that America, exerting all her enormous force will
                    insure ultimate victory for England has had a tremendous effect.</p>
                <p>I fear it may not prevent the unmolested passage of German troops through
                    Bulgaria but it very possibly may prevent the cooperation between Bulgarian and
                    German troops. Bulgaria fervently wants the continuation of America’s friendly
                    offices at the next peace conference.</p>
                <p>Donovan’s visit has been commented on very favorably in the Bulgarian press.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Earle</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
